tags.description: Mostly planted trees along an embankment, with some grass and one bench.

Designed by Alexander Marshall Mackenzie (1848-1933) and James Matthews (1819-1898). The sunken Victorian gardens opened to the public in 1879. Engulfed within the heart of Aberdeen, this park is surrounded on all sides by the city's gothic architecture.
tags.name: Union Terrace Gardens
